A MAN is due to appear in court today in connection with a wilful fire-raising at Turkish barber shop.The 47-year-old was arrested after the incident Gogo's barbers in Glasgow last month.He is currently detained in police custody and is expected to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court later today.As reported by the Evening Times, a probe was launched into the fire at the barber shop in Cambridge Street on May 17.A Police Scotland spokesman said: &quot;A 47-year-old man has been arrested in connection with an alleged wilful fire-raising in Glasgow city centre.&quot;He is currently detained in police custody.&quot;